cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the secure communication of originator and beneficiary information between VASPs, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a trust network of VASPs, which involves distributed systems and networks (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of public key certificates is also discussed, which relates to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Finally, the paper addresses the FATF Recommendations, which are related to cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
